    h2 Custom Build
    p ZaUI comes with Gulp builder that allows to build custom library version where you may include only required components/modules. We need the following:
    ol
      li
        p Download and unzip <a href="https://github.com/zmpio/zmp" target="_blank">ZaUI GitHub repository</a> to local folder
      li
        p Install <a href="http://nodejs.org/" target="_blank">Node.js</a> (if not installed)
      li
        p Install Gulp (if not installed) by executing the following command in terminal:
        :code
          $ npm install --global gulp
      li
        p Now, we need to install required dependencies. Go to the folder with downloaded and unzipped ZaUI repository and execute in terminal:
        :code
          $ npm install
      li Copy `scripts/build-config.js` file to some place in the downloaded folder and rename it let's say to `scripts/my-config.js`
