      li
        p Now, we are ready to build custom version of ZaUI. We need to execute:
        :code
          $ npm run build-core:prod -- --config scripts/my-config.js --output path/to/output/folder
      li
        p That is all. Now you should see newly generated js and css files in specified output folder

    h2 ES Modules
    p If you use bundler like Webpack or Rollup you can use only required ZaUI JS components without that build process and by importing only required components:
    :code(lang="js")
          // Import core framework
          import ZaUI from 'zmp';

          // Import additional components
          import Searchbar from 'zmp/components/searchbar';
          import Calendar from 'zmp/components/calendar';
          import Popup from 'zmp/components/popup';

          // Install F7 Components using .use() method on ZaUI class:
          ZaUI.use([Searchbar, Calendar, Popup]);

          // Init app
          var app = new ZMP({/*...*/});
